<text size = "7"><center> You know...as I headed on this journey, I thought "hey, this is going to be fun, this is going to just be easy, this is just going to be an extension of my life back in my hometown." Boy, was I wrong. Not only did I get lost a lot, but it helped me see the beauty of growing up and getting on with my life.
Not only that, but realizing that life as I know it now will NEVER be the same and everything that I thought I knew is now going to change and everything that I hope to know is now going to be attainable at a cost. Everything is at a cost....the real question is now, is it worth it.
Are my dreams worth the cost I am going to have to pay to get them? Well....in a simple word "yes" they are...and yes, I will reach them.
I will have trouble no doubt, but the outcome....will entail sweet victory.

Ok, so why is it that when life seems to be going so well, something jsut smaks you in the face, its like trying to get back on the bike/horse/whatever analogy that you want to use, but hopefully the whole picking myself back up process wont be that bad.

Tonight, my mom and I went to an aerobics class....yeah, it was...well to say in the least, challenging.  I'll be sore tomorrow.

Gah lee, I've been feeling so weird this week, I'm missing Josh like crazy.  I talked to him on Monday for like 11 mins and 53 sec. after I got off the phone I thought I was going to be all happy, but the result was just tears, I didnt want that to be the end, ya know?  Its a complicated feeling, but there isnt really any use in dwelling the the fact that I never get to see or talk to him. Sometimes, I just feel like he doesnt really like me, because of his actions, if that makes any sense, but then again, he is busy, and he has a life, but then I think, well is he to busy for a girlfriend that he cant like communicate with like once a day?  Thats just how I think sometimes, but then I tell myself that its not worth getting all sad over because thats not it.  Alrighty well...

Goodbye.

Well, I just feel like writing tonight, I dont know what about, but I just feel like getting some stuff out.

First of all school starts in like 2 days. Yes, even though I try to deny it, its still here and no matter how much I want it not to be, it is and I have to accept it.  I hate to admit it, but I am kind-of excited, its just a good feeling knowing that I am going to be an upperclassmen for the first time in my life.  Last year was great because it was all like oooh domination over the freshmen and now its like oooh domination over the sophmores and the freshmen. Nothing like being power-hungry, eh?

Second, There is the whole sister thing.  I mean dont get me wrong, I love her and I would do anything for her and I tell her a lot of things, we are like best friends and I know her and I have had to be around her all my life, but sometimes, oh man.  I just dont get it, I feel like she thinks that I am going to abandon her and i'm like no, are you crazy? I just want to smack her for thinking such thoughts and I...ahhhh.  But then again, I wouldnt be able to live without her because she knows me and she still loves me and I know that I can always go to her and she will listen to me(well sometimes) and then usually give me some sort of wisdom back on my situation.  Oh, and I HATE it when people think they know my sister better than me, for example, we had a fight a while ago and I knew it was best to just let her cool off, but no someone thought that it would be best for me to go and talk to her and I was like no, thats no a good idea, but they insisted and I did and it made it worse.Yeah, I win on that one.

Third, I am the happiest girl in the world. Why, you ask?  The reason is none other than Joshua. I love him.  I know most people are all like, you dont love him, you have only been dating for like 10 days, and I am usually one of those people, but in this situation, I feel as if I really do truely love him, its just one of those things that you cant explain.  I dont know how it happened, but I know that it did happen for a reason and I am so happy that it did.  Its different being with him, there no over-obsessiveness going on(well maybe on my part, but hey come on now), Every time I see him, I still get nervous that i'm going to say something stupid or that he wont like me, but then i'm like "well, hes liked me so far, so why not just be yourself" and then, usually its all good. That is when I do get to see him. Oh gosh, I am rambelling on and on and I cannot spell worth anything.

Fourth, I love Maria.  I have never been this close to anyone thats not related to me, but we are one person, so ya know.  I would have never made it through high school without her right there.  She stuck with me through all the STUPID crap that I have dragged her through, and good lord, she is tough.  Oh the good times weve had, Oh yes, Mr Millsaps I still remember him and the rendouvxes weve had, yes yes, good times. Oh, and Kashi trail mix bars, yes and staying up till ten and sleeping on my computer and taking crazy pictures and sleeping outside and doing fun crazy stuff and I love her!

Well, I would be suprised if anyone was still reading this because its like the longest entry that I prob have ever like typed, but ya know, sometimes you just need to get your feelings out and thats ok.

Ok, Fifth, Why do people have to be stupid?  I know that i'm not the brightest one at times, but really come on.  Some people just give off that stupid vibe and your like good lord, whats the deal man.  It rather drives me insane, ya know?

Well, Jons party was fun.  Maybe I need to work on my soccer skills a tad, but I wasnt really trying for the record, and oh yes,  Ri discovered that sitting on my car was like perfect for stargazing, so i'm going to keep that one in mind. 

If you want something so badly then why dont you just go for it???? I'd like to ask that question to some people, gah, it makes me mad, but whatever.

Well, I have work tomorrow and its already like midnight, whooo. I;m going to get some sleep, well at least try to.  Ok, well peace out.

\\goodnight.
